  "@type": "Article",
  "dateModified": "2026-03-03",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-03",
  "description": "The refusal of work is the central practice theorized by operaismo and autonomism: the claim that the most radical form of class struggle is not the seizure of the means of production but the withdrawal of labor itself — the refusal to be productive on capital\u0026rsquo;s terms. This refusal takes many forms: absenteeism, slowdowns, sabotage, wildcat strikes, the rejection of workplace discipline, and the construction of forms of life that do not depend on the wage.\n",
  "name": "Refusal of Work",
